This paper discusses the state of the art in power line communication (PLC) technology, which involves the transmission of data over power lines. This topic is relevant to several computer science sub-categories, including networked systems (cs.NI), information theory (cs.IT), communication and networking (cs.COMM), systems and control (cs.SY), and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper covers a range of topics related to PLC, including channel characterization, physical layer performance, medium access, and higher layer specifications and evaluations, which are relevant to these sub-categories. Therefore, it is likely that this paper could be classified under any of these sub-categories, with cs.NI and cs.IT being the most likely due to their focus on networked systems and information theory, respectively.
